A cleric, Ven. Feyi Ojelabi, on Sunday, called on fathers to ensure that all eligible members of their households obtained their  Permanent Voters Card (PVC) for the 2023 elections. Ojelabi, the Archdeacon of Holy Trinity Anglican Church, Ikate, Lagos made the call to mark this year’s Father’s Day celebration. Pregnant woman, corps member, 5 others drown in Bayelsa boat crash No part of Nigeria is safe again, Gani Adams tells UN, EU, others He urged fathers to ensure every member of their family obtain their PVC to vote in the forthcoming elections irrespective of their beliefs. NAN